    "John Trapp": "Seal not ] Keep them not up for thine own proper use (as he did that wrote upon his writings, \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03bc\u03b1\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd, things for myself), but freely impart t hem, and in such sort as that others may conceive and improve them.\nVer.\n10. Seal not] Keep them not up for thine own proper use (as he did that wrote upon his writings, \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03bc\u03b1\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd, things for myself), but freely impart them, and in such sort as that others may conceive and improve them.\nVer."
